The esophagus is a muscular tube connecting the pharynx and the stomach. It consists of 4 layers typical of the general structure of the alimentary canal:

tunica mucosa (mucosa);
tela submucosa (submucosa);
tunica muscularis externa (external muscle);
adventitia + serosa.

